CIX Sky1 ACPI: defer known clock consumers until CLKT lookups exist

The Sky1 ACPI clock lookup provider is populated from firmware CLKT tables
after the SCMI clock provider is available. Several Sky1 ACPI consumers probe
before that point and treat missing clock lookups as fatal -ENOENT, leaving
the devices permanently unbound even though their clocks appear later.

For known Sky1 ACPI devices, convert missing mandatory clocks to
-EPROBE_DEFER. This preserves real errors after suppliers are available while
allowing normal driver-core retry ordering when ACPI clock mappings are still
being registered.

diff --git a/drivers/clk/cix/clk-sky1-audss.c b/drivers/clk/cix/clk-sky1-audss.c
--- a/drivers/clk/cix/clk-sky1-audss.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/cix/clk-sky1-audss.c
@@ -730,9 +730,14 @@ static int sky1_audss_clk_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	/* Get parent clocks from SCMI */
 	for (i = 0; i < SKY1_AUDSS_CLKS_NUM; i++) {
 		priv->parent_clks[i] = devm_clk_get(dev, sky1_audss_clk_names[i]);
-		if (IS_ERR(priv->parent_clks[i]))
-			return dev_err_probe(dev, PTR_ERR(priv->parent_clks[i]),
+		if (IS_ERR(priv->parent_clks[i])) {
+			ret = PTR_ERR(priv->parent_clks[i]);
+			if (ret == -ENOENT && has_acpi_companion(dev))
+				ret = -EPROBE_DEFER;
+
+			return dev_err_probe(dev, ret,
 					     "failed to get %s\n", sky1_audss_clk_names[i]);
+		}
 	}
 
 	/* Allocate clock data */
